text.__SUMMARY__: Conus nelsonandradoi (or Africonus nelsonandradoi), is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.These snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans.
text.Distribution:
This marine species occurs in the Atlantic Ocean off Sal Island, the Cape Verdes.
